 {"id":"bd-tmio1","title":"CONFORMANCE: libc termios.h diff matrix","description":"Differential harness shipped (see commit). 6 functions (cfgetispeed/cfgetospeed/cfsetispeed/cfsetospeed/tcgetattr/tcsetattr), 7 tests. Covers 10 baud rates round-trip, PTY tcgetattr/tcsetattr, ENOTTY on non-tty fd. Discovered DISC-TERMIOS-001: fl uses TCGETS, glibc uses TCGETS2 — CIBAUD bits in c_cflag stripped by fl. Also documented POSIX-implementation-defined divergence in cfsetispeed invalid-speed handling.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-frankenlibc","created_at":"2026-04-24T09:30:00Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T09:30:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T09:30:00Z","close_reason":"Harness shipped; CIBAUD divergence (DISC-TERMIOS-001) handled via mask-and-log; cfsetispeed invalid-speed divergence documented as POSIX implementation-defined.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","differential","termios"]}
 {"id":"bd-tmio2","title":"FIX: tcgetattr/tcsetattr should use TCGETS2/TCSETS2 to preserve CIBAUD","description":"Discovered by termios.h conformance harness (DISC-TERMIOS-001). Modern glibc uses TCGETS2 which preserves CIBAUD (input baud) bits in c_cflag (mask 0x100f0000); fl currently uses TCGETS which loses them. Fix: switch to TCGETS2 with struct termios2 and copy fields back to user's struct termios. Affects: termios_abi.rs:561 tcgetattr, ~620 tcsetattr.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cod-frankenlibc","created_at":"2026-04-24T09:30:00Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T09:31:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T09:31:00Z","close_reason":"Switched termios attr ioctls to TCGETS2/TCSETS2 and pinned CIBAUD parity","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["bug","conformance","termios"]}
 {"id":"bd-tpnv","title":"Execute dlfcn_ops fixture through isolated harness","description":"Upgrade dlfcn_ops conformance from schema-only validation to per-case isolated harness execution, plus top-level fixture metadata assertions.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-04-17T00:08:04.151105227Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-17T00:12:22.107050748Z","closed_at":"2026-04-17T00:12:22.104109338Z","close_reason":"Upgraded dlfcn_ops conformance coverage to execute each fixture case through the isolated harness subprocess path and added fixture metadata assertions.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-ts3l3","title":"PORT: getbsize (BSD libutil block-size header)","description":"BSD libutil getbsize(headerlenp, blocksizep) reads the BLOCKSIZE environment variable (parsing optional k/K/m/M/g/G suffix as 1024-multiplier), clamps the block size to [512, 1<<30], and returns a pointer to static storage containing the matching header string (\"512-blocks\", \"1K-blocks\", \"1M-blocks\", \"1G-blocks\"). Used by df(1), du(1), ls(1) and other BSD utilities to render block counts in user-friendly units. Currently missing entirely from frankenlibc-abi. Ship: pure-safe core::stdlib::getbsize::resolve_blocksize parsing the env-var byte slice + format header bytes, plus a thin abi shim in stdlib_abi.rs that reads getenv(\"BLOCKSIZE\"), calls into core, and stores the result in a OnceLock<[u8; 32]> static buffer for the static-pointer return.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T15:33:38.938211866Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T15:33:38.938211866Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-ttwfr","title":"syscall: pidfd_getfd self pidfd invalid targetfd plus invalid flags should return EINVAL exactly","description":"Host glibc returns EINVAL for pidfd_getfd(self_pidfd, -1, 1). Add focused ABI regression coverage for the precedence of invalid flags over invalid targetfd on a valid pidfd.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T10:49:44.633103944Z","created_by":"AmberSignal","updated_at":"2026-04-22T05:02:44.577658938Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T05:02:44.575073378Z","close_reason":"pidfd_getfd(self, -1, 1) → EINVAL (flags validation wins over bad targetfd) pinned.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-tvug","title":"Complementary mount-family veneer error tests (open_tree/fsmount/mount_setattr)","description":"Cod's bd-rp9r (commit e6e612a) added syscall number + signature pins for 7 mount-namespace syscalls plus 2 error tests (setns/unshare). The other 5 new-mount-API veneers (open_tree, move_mount, fsopen, fsmount, mount_setattr) have signature pins but no error-path smoke test. Add 3 safe deterministic negative cases: fsmount(-1) EBADF, mount_setattr(-1) EBADF, open_tree with invalid args. Scope: crates/frankenlibc-core/tests/syscall_veneer_test.rs x86_64_tests module.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-20T21:44:14.055742372Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-20T21:47:07.830578229Z","closed_at":"2026-04-20T21:47:07.828619061Z","close_reason":"Added 4 complementary mount-family error-path tests in commit 280ffe2: fsmount(-1), mount_setattr(-1), open_tree(-1, NULL), fsopen(NULL). Together with cod's setns/unshare coverage (bd-rp9r), the 7 new-mount-API veneers now have signature pins + 6 error-path smoke tests. All accept ENOSYS/EPERM so containers/kernels without the new mount API pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-tw26d","title":"[fuzz-harness] fuzz_socket: MarkStale left s.fd so kernel could reuse the fd for a new slot, breaking shutdown-fails invariant","description":"Found and fixed in this solo session via systematic deep-fuzz sweeps. Fix shipped in 756dcfb1. Filing retroactively per Tick-95 request to track each harness defect explicitly. Not a library bug — the frankenlibc ABI was correct throughout; only the fuzz harness invariants needed tightening.","notes":"Fixed in 756dcfb1 — MarkStale poisons s.fd to -1 so kernel fd reuse can't break stale-must-fail invariant.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-23T16:29:04.692971736Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-23T16:36:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T16:36:00Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
